 dominate social relations. Chaturvedi suggests that this littletold story is necessary to understand not only anticolonial nationalism but the direction of postcolonial nationalism as well.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aDharalasxHistoryy19th centuryxHistoriography. 0aDharalasxHistoryy20th centuryxHistoriography. 0aDharalasxPolitical activity. 0aDharalasxSocial conditionsy19th century. 0aDharalasxSocial conditionsy20th century. 0aNationalismzIndiazGujaratxHistoriography. 7aHISTORY / Asia / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520940598423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520940598.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles